Nusrat Jahan (নুসরত জাহান) is an Indian Bengali film actress and also worked as a model. She is one of the most beautiful and popular Bengali movies. She also joined in politics in 2019 and she is the Member of Lok Sabha from Basirhat Constituency from Trinamool Congress.

Biography & Wiki

Nusrat Jahan’s nickname is Nusrat. She was born on 8th January 1990 in Kolkata, India. Hence, her current age is 30 years. Nusrat Zodiac is Capricorn.

Family Members

Nusrat is a very gorgeous actress who belongs to a Bengali Muslim family. She has two sisters named Nuzhat Jahan and Pooja Prasad. Her father and mother’s names are not available.

Boys, affairs, spouse name

First of all, She was in a serious relationship with Kader Khan and they broke up after Kader got arrested for a serious criminal case. After that, there was a rumor that she was in a relationship with a businessman from Jamshedpur called Victor Ghosh.

Nusrat got married to Nikhil Jain in Turkey on 19th June 2019. Nikhil is the director of a leading trader of clothes from Kolkata. Consequently, he completed his initial study from Kolkata. According to media Nusrat and Nikhil met in the advertisement set of this company.

Nusrat Jahan filmography

First of all, Nusrat has also won the title of Fair One Miss Kolkata in 2010. Her first screen debut was in Raj Chakraborty’s Shotru. After that, she appeared as a movie actress in the film Khoka 420, under the banner Eskay Movies. Apart from this movie, the other notable movies where she worked an actress are Khiladi with Ankush Hazra, Sondhe Namar Agey with Rahul Bose and Power with Jeet under the banner of Shree Venkatesh Films.

Politics

West Bengal Chief Minister and president of Trinamool Congress party Mamata Banerjee announced Nusrat as a candidate for the Lok Sabha election 2019. Finally, Nusrat won an election from Basirhat Constituency. She won by a margin of 3.5 lakh votes.

Salary and Net Worth

Nusrat owns two cars. The total cost of these two cars is Rs. 35 lakh 50 thousand. Nusrat has 450 grams of gold and diamond jewelry. The total value of her jewelry is Rs.12 lakhs. Nusrat’s immovable property amounting to Rs.2 crore.

Education and School, College

She has completed her schooling from Our Lady Queen of the Missions School in Kolkata. Later on completed her B.Com. degree from Bhawanipur College, Kolkata.
